#style.use

from matplotlib import style
style.use('ggplot')
x=[10,12,14,16,18]
y=[20,22,24,26,28]

x1=[17,23,39,45,59]
y1=[45,78,43,56,68]

plt.plot(x,y,'g', label='sales',linewidth=10)
plt.plot(x1,y1,'y', label='profit', linewidth=6)
plt.title('using style')
plt.xlabel('X-axis')
plt.ylabel('Y-axis')
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True, color='b')

In [62]:
#mutliple graphs
x1=np.arange(10,30,2)
y1 = [1,5,6,7,8,3,4,6,5,4]

x2= np.arange (10,30,2)
y2 = [5,4,2,8,4,6,3,4,5,4]

plt.subplot (211)
plt.plot(x1,y1)
plt.title ('Graph 1')
plt.xlabel ('X-Axis')
plt.ylabel ('Y-Axis')

plt.subplot(212)
plt.plot(x2,y2)
plt.title ('Graph 2')
plt.xlabel ('X-Axis')
plt.ylabel ('Y-Axis')
plt.tight_layout(pad=1,h_pad = 1, w_pad = 1)

plt.show()
